title: Elephant completes epic Nullarbor journey to new home | 7NEWS
description: A 35-year-old male Asian elephant named Putra Mass has completed a 2,700 kilometre journey from Perth to South Australia's Monarto Safari Park. The 4.7 tonne bull elephant travelled for 30 hours across the Nullarbor in a specially designed crate to join a herd of four female Asian elephants. Putra Mass becomes the fifth and final elephant at the safari park, where he will reunite with Permai from Perth Zoo and meet three other females who recently arrived from Auckland Zoo and Taronga Zoo. title: Perth tourist loses $400 to airport Wi-Fi scam | 7NEWS
description: Cyber criminals are exploiting public Wi-Fi networks during the festive season, with a Perth tourist losing $400 from her bank account after connecting to free airport Wi-Fi. Scammers use 'evil twin' fake hotspots that mimic legitimate airport or cafÃ© networks to capture passwords and redirect users to fraudulent payment forms. Security experts recommend using mobile data or personal hotspots instead of public Wi-Fi, enabling multi-factor authentication, and immediately changing passwords if suspicious activity is detected.
